title: Narrative

* This example shows ''programmatic branch control'' using buttons

* The `toc-openBranch` and `toc-closeBranch` procedures accept a `manual:"yes"` parameter

* "Open whole Tree" recursively opens all branches from Contents

* "Close branch: bb" closes only the bb branch and its children

* <kbd>CTRL</kbd>-clicking a chevron has the same effect

{{example-overview}}

+
title: Description

Programmatic Branch Open/Close Buttons
+
title: Output

\procedure closeBranch()
<<toc-closeBranch path:"/Contents" currentTiddler:"bb" manual:yes>>
\end

\procedure openBranch()
<<toc-openBranch path:"/" currentTiddler:"Contents" manual:yes>>
\end

<$button actions=<<openBranch>>>Open whole Tree</$button>

<$button actions=<<closeBranch>>>Close branch: bb</$button>

<div class="tc-table-of-contents">
<<toc-selective-expandable tag:"Contents">>
</div>